sample_record.title: Welcome to Coach Will's Adventure Journal
sample_record.content:
Welcome to our adventure journal! Here, we document the incredible journeys of young gymnasts as they discover their strength, grace, and confidence through the art of gymnastics.

Every athlete who steps into our gym begins their own unique adventure. Whether they're taking their first tumbling pass or perfecting an advanced skill, each moment is a chance to grow, learn, and discover something new about themselves.

In this journal, you'll find stories of triumph, lessons learned, and the magic that happens when dedication meets dreams. Our goal is to support not just the physical development of each athlete, but their confidence, character, and love for the sport.

Welcome to the adventure!

sample_record.question: What age should my child start gymnastics?
sample_record.answer: Most kids are ready by age 4 or 5 — especially if they're constantly moving, flipping off the couch, or can't sit still. We adapt to each child's pace.

sample_record.name: Mike Johnson
sample_record.text: Professional, patient, and passionate about gymnastics. Our son loves his lessons and we've seen incredible progress in his strength and coordination.

sample_record.title: Perfect Cartwheel Quest
sample_record.content: The cartwheel is a fundamental skill that builds strength, coordination, and confidence. Master this move to unlock more advanced tumbling adventures!

sections.title: Step 1: Hand Placement
sections.content: Start with hands reaching up high, then place them on the floor shoulder-width apart. Think of creating a strong foundation for your wheel!

sections.title: Step 2: The Kick-Over
sections.content: Kick your legs over in a straight line, keeping your body sideways like a wheel. Remember: legs stay straight and strong!

sections.title: Step 3: The Landing
sections.content: Land one foot at a time, finishing with arms up in a victory pose! Control is key for a perfect finish.

sections.title: Practice Tip
sections.content: Start on a line to keep your cartwheel straight and true. The line is your guide to adventure!
